ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This was an excellent course that introduced students to a range of manuscripts, manuscript problems, and aspects of early book production.
For any medievalist who wishes to be a professional researcher, this class is obligatory, providing and training a range of essential research skills.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course helped me better understand the production process of medieval texts, especially religious compilations.
The skills taught in this course are skills every professional medievalist should have. I would consider myself incompletely formed as a scholar without them.
